Alan Shearer surprised by Fabio Capello resignation
Media playback is not supported on this deviceFormer England captain Alan Shearer says he is "shocked" and "amazed" byFabio Capello's decision to resign as England managerand urges the Football Association to appoint an Englishman as his successor.Speaking toBBC Radio 5 live, Shearer says he is surprised most by the timing of Capello's decision because he feels England have a really good chance of doing well at Euro 2012.The former England striker says the departure of Capello will not really affect the players as they will want to play for their country whoever is in charge.He also says Tottenham boss Harry Redknapp is the leading candidate to replace the Italian, whose reign lasted just over four years.